AttributeSet.Attribute: Myriad Autosomal Dominant, Autosomal Recessive and X-Linked Classification Criteria (2023)

Classification.Comment: For these reasons, this variant has been classified as Pathogenic. This variant has not been reported in the literature in individuals affected with MSH6-related conditions. This variant is not present in population databases (gnomAD no frequency). This sequence change creates a premature translational stop signal (p.Lys1014Glufs*4) in the MSH6 gene. It is expected to result in an absent or disrupted protein product. Loss-of-function variants in MSH6 are known to be pathogenic (PMID: 18269114, 24362816).
